<!-- PJG ITAG l=81 g=1 f=1 -->
(4) Demonstration That Progress Requirements for 1990&hyph;2000 Are 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Met Without the Need for Section 182(e)(5) Measure Reductions 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG /ITAG -->

<!-- PJG ITAG l=11 g=1 f=1 -->
As discussed above, section 182(e)(5) provides that an 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
attainment demonstration can rely on new technology commitments 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
if the measures are shown not to be needed to achieve the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
incremental emission reductions required during the first 10 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
years after the date of enactment of the Clean Air Act Amendments 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of 1990. Section 182(e)(5) contains no requirement that this 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
demonstration be based exclusively on adopted and submitted 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
measures. Section 182(e)(5) explicitly states that the showing 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
need be only ``to the satisfaction of the Administrator.'' EPA 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
must be able to conclude, however, that the State has the ability 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
to meet the progress requirements without relying on the new 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
technology measures. 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Elsewhere in this NPRM (see section II.C.2.), EPA describes 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
the recently submitted South Coast Rate-of-Progress Plan, which 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
demonstrates achievement of the progress requirements for the 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
first 6 years primarily through fully adopted State and local 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
measures. To the extent that the demonstration rests on measures 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
not yet fully adopted, EPA cannot now propose to accept the plan 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
for purposes of satisfying the 15 percent reduction requirement 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
of section 182(b)(1), in conformance with the referenced EPA 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
policy memorandum, ``Guidance on Issues Related to 15 Percent 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->
Rate-of-Progress Plans'' (August 23, 1993). 
<!-- PJG 0012 frnewline -->

